window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>How have you dealt with the trauma of your parents’ divorce or broken family? </p><p><br></p><p>After enduring her parents’ divorce, her mom’s alcoholism, her dad’s absence, and her stepmom’s abuse, today’s guest tried to outrun her trauma through busyness, accomplishments, and perfectionism. </p><p><br></p><p>Before long, she went from repressing her emotions and saying “I’m fine” to “I need help.” That began her healing, which we discuss, plus:</p><ul><li>How she doubted her ability to be a good wife and mother</li><li>How she grew up faster than her peers from intact families, making it difficult to relate to them</li><li>When are anxiety or depression drugs necessary and when are they used inappropriately?</li></ul><p><br></p><p>Join the Course Waitlist</p><p><br></p><p>Take the My Broken Family Assessment</p><p><br></p><p>Share Your Story</p><p><br></p><p>Shownotes</p><p><br><br></p>"; 
